1 (b) The name, business address, discipline^ and specialty
2 of the qualified health care provider and reasons for the
3 functional capacity examination shall be submitted in writing to
4 the employer at least seven calendar days before the referral.
5 (c) The qualified health care provider performing the
6 functional capacity examination shall provide a copy of the
7 functional capacity examination report to the attending
8 physician and employer no later than fourteen calendar days
9 after the date of the examination.
10 (d) Fees for functional capacity examinations requested by
11 the attending physician pursuant to this section shall be paid
12 by the employer.
13 (e) As used in this section:
14 "Functional capacity examination" means a set of tests that
15 are used to identify an injured employee's physical skills,
16 functional capabilities, activity endurance, and work tolerances
17 after reaching medical stabilization.
18 "Functional capacity examination report" means a report
19 issued by a qualified health care provider that provides
20 recommendations regarding an injured employee's ability to
21 return to work with or without restrictions or the need for
2026-3317 HB1515 CDl HMSO

