1 accommodations to safely return to work based on a functional
2 capacity examination performed on the injured employee.
3 "Qualified health care provider" means a health care
4 provider who meets the qualifications under section 386-27 to
5 render health care and services under this chapter."
6 SECTION 3. Section 386-1, Hawaii Revised Statutes, is
7 amended by amending the definition of "health care provider" to
8 read as follows:
9 ""Health care provider" means a person qualified by the
10 director to render health care and service and who has a license
11 for the practice of:
12 (1) Medicine or [os-tcopathy] osteopathic medicine under
13 chapter 453;
14 (2) Dentistry under chapter 448;
15 (3) Chiropractic under chapter 442;
16 (4) Naturopathic medicine under chapter 455;
17 (5) Optometry under chapter 459;
18 (6) Podiatry under chapter 463E;
19 (7) Psychology under chapter 465; [and]
20 (8) Advanced practice registered nurse under chapter
